cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on visual tracking using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with video processing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
